 href=\"https://www.polygon.com/2015/3/25/8284763/how-pillars-of-eternity-rewrites-the-rules-for-role-playing\"\u003ePillars of Eternity: Definitive Edition\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/em\u003e, \u003cem\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://www.polygon.com/2019/1/23/18194374/pillars-of-eternity-2-deadfire-preview-impressions\"\u003ePillars of Eternity 2: Obsidian Edition\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/em\u003e, \u003cem\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://www.polygon.com/reviews/23053260/citizen-sleeper-review-cyberpunk-sci-fi-rpg-tabletop\"\u003eCitizen Sleeper\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/em\u003e, \u003cem\u003eBroken Roads\u003c/em\u003e, and \u003cem\u003eRoadwarden\u003c/em\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cp\u003eThe Pillars of Eternity franchise offers a high-fantasy, isometric CRPG experience similar to the classic Baldur’s Gate titles. And would you believe it’s still in development 10 years after release? The devs just dropped \u003ca href=\"https://forums.obsidian.net/topic/134573-patch-138087535-is-live/\"\u003ea turn-based update\u003c/a\u003e for the original that brings it in line with \u003ca href=\"https://www.polygon.com/2019/1/23/18194374/pillars-of-eternity-2-deadfire-preview-impressions\"\u003ethe upgraded sequel\u003c/a\u003e. Meanwhile, \u003cem\u003eBroken Roads\u003c/em\u003e puts an original spin on post-apocalyptic role-playing.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eIn addition to this collection of six other CRPGs, you’ll also get a 15% off coupon to purchase \u003cem\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://www.polygon.com/review/515847/citizen-sleeper-2-starward-vector-review\"\u003eCitizen Sleeper 2\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/em\u003e from Steam, reducing the usual $25 price to $21.25.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cdiv data-product-filter=\"\"\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://humblebundleinc.sjv.io/c/482924/2091208/25796?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.humblebundle.com%2Fgames%2Fdice-and-destiny%3Fhmb_source%3D%26hmb_medium%3Dproduct_tile%26hmb_campaign%3Dmosaic_section_1_layout_index_1_layout_type_threes_tile_index_